cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use the PARALLAX-5 AI-FV Co-Pilot in academic work, please cite both this software and the underlying substrate."
type: software
title: "PARALLAX-5 AI-FV Co-Pilot: LLM-Drafted, Kernel-Verified Smart-Contract Proofs"
abstract: >-
  An AI-assisted formal-verification co-pilot specialized to the PARALLAX-5
  five-obligation substrate for smart-contract security. Four frontier
  language models (Claude, GPT, Deepseek, Mistral Leanstral) draft
  obligation-typed Lean 4 specifications and proofs for Solidity
  contracts; the Lean kernel decides which drafts are accepted. The
  co-pilot does not create trust; it accelerates property authoring
  and proof drafting whose outputs admit kernel verification.
authors:
  - name: "AquaUrsa Research"
    website: "https://aquaursa.io"
version: "0.1.0"
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/aquaursa/parallax5-aifv-copilot"
keywords:
  - formal verification
  - Lean 4
  - AI-assisted theorem proving
  - smart contract security
  - PARALLAX-5
  - large language models
references:
  - type: software
    title: "PARALLAX-5: A Five-Obligation Substrate for Smart Contracts and AI Agents"
    doi: 10.5281/zenodo.20402755
    notes: "Underlying substrate. The co-pilot extends PARALLAX-5 from abstract-layer mechanization to per-contract certification."
